data.description: **Back on the market to no fault of the sellers.** This charming three-bedroom brick home, located in the Pace School district, sits on a generously sized lot. As you enter, a welcoming foyer complete with a convenient coat closet greets you. The spacious great room features a cathedral ceiling, a tile fireplace with an elegant mantle as well as plant ledges. It's designed for comfort and relaxation, with a TV/entertainment nook and sliding glass doors that open to a delightful patio. Ceiling fans throughout the home provide an added touch of comfort. For those special occasions, there's a formal dining room. The island kitchen is a highlight, boasting a breakfast bar and a cozy nook. You'll find a vegetable sink, a walk-in pantry, and cabinets that add character and functionality to the space. The kitchen is equipped with a self-cleaning electric range and a reliable Kenmore dishwasher. The convenience continues with an inside laundry area. The master suite is thoughtfully located on the other side of the house, providing a sense of privacy. It includes a spacious walk-in closet and an inviting master bath with a garden tub, a separate shower, and a double vanity. The guest bedrooms are equally comfortable and feature ceiling fans. The hall bathroom includes a linen closet for additional storage. To accommodate your vehicles and provide convenience, there's a two-car side entry garage. Outside, the yard is enclosed with a privacy fence, offering a secure and private space for outdoor activities. This home is a wonderful opportunity for those seeking a comfortable and spacious living environment.
